cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.HC 

This paper is about developing agents for engaging in complex goal-oriented dialogues. The main focus is on discovering and exploiting the hidden structure of the task to enable efficient policy learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a Subgoal Discovery Network (SDN) to divide a complex goal-oriented task into a set of simpler subgoals, which involves machine learning techniques and can be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the human comprehensibility of the learned subgoals, which falls under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper involves the use of reinforcement learning, which can be categorized under cs.SD (Systems and Control).
